  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut the<strong> aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half lengthways (including the stalk), then score the flesh in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut through to the skin</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine halves</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 30-35 min or until very tender – this is your <strong>roasted aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685091526404-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685091526404-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685091526404-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685091526404-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1685091526404-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pot (with a lid) over a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cumin seeds </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685091529696-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685091529696-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685091529696-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685091529696-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685091529696-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685091531992-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685091531992-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685091531992-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685091531992-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685091531992-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!),<strong> </strong>season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685091534761-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
