          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685091534761-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>ras el hanout</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for a further 4-5 min or until thickened and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Turkish-style ali nazik beef kebab</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1685091537667-x200.jpg",
